subject: Load tenant un-lazily if needed
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-17 05:34:11.000000000', 'files': ['lib/puppet/provider/keystone_user_role/keystone.rb'], 'message': 'Load tenant un-lazily if needed

The laziness added to the role to reduce keystone
lookups assumes that all tenants are present in @tenants
if they are present in the system, and will not refresh
the class variable if the tenant is not found in it.

This patch adds a keystone lookup in the event of the supplied
tenant not being in the class variable, which can happen if a
tenant is created after prefetching.

Change-Id: I48b13f6abc906cde4794dd46d7938126aae204b1
'}]
commit_message:
Load tenant un-lazily if needed

The laziness added to the role to reduce keystone
lookups assumes that all tenants are present in @tenants
if they are present in the system, and will not refresh
the class variable if the tenant is not found in it.

This patch adds a keystone lookup in the event of the supplied
tenant not being in the class variable, which can happen if a
tenant is created after prefetching.

Change-Id: I48b13f6abc906cde4794dd46d7938126aae204b1

commit_message:
Add --segment support to net-create

This change allow to create network with multiple segment from the cli

Example:

 neutron net-create multi-provider \
  --segment provider:network_type=vlan,provider:physical_network=physnet1,provider:segmentation_id=1000
  --segment provider:network_type=vlan,provider:physical_network=physnet2,provider:segmentation_id=2000

Closes-Bug: #1271847

Change-Id: I68b9f4a54ae4305fe3c38204d50fe378ffd16dfb

commit_message:
Move image transfer code in VMware drivers to OSLO

There is lot of common code between VMware drivers for nova and cinder;
for e.g., session management and VIM API invocation code. The new
VMware driver for glance and the telemetry agent for vSphere are also
planning to use this common code. This change moves methods and classes
for image transfer between VMware servers and the image service into
OSLO.

Change-Id: I527122c99b3a03fca6bb22e4817771c91c1a023d
Implements: blueprint vmware-api

Add model_query() to db.sqlalchemy.utils module

commit_message:
Interactive prompt for create user

Execution of the shell will now prompt the user for a password if argument
'--pass' is specified without a following parameter.  In that way, a user does
not need to pass passwords on the command line.

Usage example:
$ keystone user-create --name bob --tenant admin --pass --enabled true
New Password:
Repeat New Password:

Closes-Bug: #1100116
Change-Id: I1f6d6322830972dfad19ebe2fe63e91f82ed8033

commit_message:
Fix apt_repository chefspec tests

Before this change, we used step_into to test the resources that are
used inside the apt_repository resource, i.e. the files it creates.
This posed a problem on non-Debian-derived OSes for the Ceph repo.

Now both tests, for the ubuntu-cloud and the ceph repo, are testing the
apt_repository resource.

Change-Id: I7d213abd8c572664053ed53412e97346e881b4c2
Closes-Bug: #1282996

commit_message:
Add remove external lock files API in lockutils

when external lock are used, there will be a lock files which
is used for external file lock, it will not be removed and remain
forever. it will be a problem when tens of thousands of this kind
of actions. Add a API to allow other component to remove lock file
internal lock will be acquired before further action

Change-Id: I4d996b91bcc55becb0ebf4ec77ac80546f433ae9
Closes-Bug: 1256306

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-01-23 08:35:50.000000000', 'files': ['hacking/core.py'], 'message': "Enhance H233 rule

Python 2 use a single 'print' to print empty line, but Python 3
doesn't support print operator, we should use print() instead.

For now, H233 cannot detect the \bprint$ problem, this patch fixes
it by adding a new pattern of regular expression.

Change-Id: Ic7031fa4e92b2ad84e81795be54698d7a9a7725c
"}]
commit_message:
Enhance H233 rule

Python 2 use a single 'print' to print empty line, but Python 3
doesn't support print operator, we should use print() instead.

For now, H233 cannot detect the \bprint$ problem, this patch fixes
it by adding a new pattern of regular expression.

Change-Id: Ic7031fa4e92b2ad84e81795be54698d7a9a7725c

subject: More portable way to detect modules for H302
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2014-01-28 07:37:28.000000000', 'files': ['hacking/core.py'], 'message': 'More portable way to detect modules for H302

Instead of analysing string representation of import exception we
try harder to import the thing and then look it up in sys.modules
-- if it was module it should be already there. This solution should
be more portable across python versions and implementations,
including Python 3 and PyPy.

Change-Id: I054968f78966961fcb72c744193092696235eafa
'}]
commit_message:
More portable way to detect modules for H302

Instead of analysing string representation of import exception we
try harder to import the thing and then look it up in sys.modules
-- if it was module it should be already there. This solution should
be more portable across python versions and implementations,
including Python 3 and PyPy.

Change-Id: I054968f78966961fcb72c744193092696235eafa

generally used. Now that we have mock and fixture, we no longer

subject: Normalize Scheduler Weights
revisions:
[{'number': 5, 'created': '2014-02-06 12:09:03.000000000', 'files': ['openstack/common/scheduler/base_weight.py', 'tests/unit/scheduler/test_weights.py'], 'message': 'Normalize Scheduler Weights

Currently we are using the raw values directly from the available
weighers instead of normalizing them. This makes difficult to
properly use multipliers for establishing the relative importance
between two weighters (one big magnitude will shade a smaller one).

Changes introduced in this commit:
1) It introduces weight normalization so that we can apply multipliers
easily. All the weights for an object will be normalized between 0.0
and 1.0 before being sumed up, so that the final weight for a host
will be:

weight = w1_multiplier * norm(w1) + w2_multiplier * norm(w2) + ...

2) base_weight.BaseWeigher has been changed into an ABC so that we
enforce that all weighers have the expected methods.

3) base_weight.BaseWeigher.weigh_objects() does no longer sum up the
computer weighs to the object, but it rather returns a list that will
be then normalized and added to the existing weight by BaseWeightHandler.

4) Change _weight_multiplier() to weight_multiplier() as a public method

Port from I81bf90898d3cb81541f4390596823cc00106eb20
Related to bp nova-oslo-scheduler

Change-Id: I1b0c7a6e141eee699a191f8a59db90d063eb31ba
Implements part of bp normalize-scheduler-weights
'}]
commit_message:
Normalize Scheduler Weights

Currently we are using the raw values directly from the available
weighers instead of normalizing them. This makes difficult to
properly use multipliers for establishing the relative importance
between two weighters (one big magnitude will shade a smaller one).

Changes introduced in this commit:
1) It introduces weight normalization so that we can apply multipliers
easily. All the weights for an object will be normalized between 0.0
and 1.0 before being sumed up, so that the final weight for a host
will be:

weight = w1_multiplier * norm(w1) + w2_multiplier * norm(w2) + ...

2) base_weight.BaseWeigher has been changed into an ABC so that we
enforce that all weighers have the expected methods.

3) base_weight.BaseWeigher.weigh_objects() does no longer sum up the
computer weighs to the object, but it rather returns a list that will
be then normalized and added to the existing weight by BaseWeightHandler.

4) Change _weight_multiplier() to weight_multiplier() as a public method

Port from I81bf90898d3cb81541f4390596823cc00106eb20
Related to bp nova-oslo-scheduler

Change-Id: I1b0c7a6e141eee699a191f8a59db90d063eb31ba
Implements part of bp normalize-scheduler-weights

commit_message:
Fix neutron package install

Previously the neutron element was installing neutron-server. This
should actually be happening in the neutron-server element itself.
Likewise, the neutron-dhcp-agent should also install the package it
needs. In both cases, the package is just openstack-neutron, but only
the intended services will be enabled and started due to the
os-refresh-config scripts. E.g., if you only include neutron-dhcp-agent,
and not neuton-server, only the neutron-dhcp-agent will be enabled.

Change-Id: I11e52e9cdd6062b03d389971acad1c52a9cc3ea8

commit_message:
Fixing issue with VXLAN network profile create

This encompases the fix for bug 1229808 which requires change in
arguments to the network_profile_create API to create overlay
profiles instead of vxlan profiles.
Additionally overlay profiles now have a new parameter called
profile sub_types which lets one specify which type of overlay
profile can be created. This adds the new parameter as well.

Closes-bug: #1229808

Change-Id: I5f5153533533b0d760c04da33abf831d95f06ea4

commit_message:
Replace stack_get_all_by_tenant with stack_get_all

Preparing the database for the unscoped list stacks, this removes
stack_get_all_by_tenant in favor of a single function that is tenant
aware.  This way, you can call stack_get_all(tenant_safe=False) and get
all stacks, regardless of the tenants.

tenant_safe defaults to True.

Implements: blueprint management-api (partial)
Change-Id: Ifdcfc44a3483a089ae803cfd044151262957674a

commit_message:
Do not use openstack clients as a thread safe objects

OpenStack python clients are not thread safe so we are not able
to share them between different processes.

This patches makes next:

* removes __openstack__clients__ and __admin_clients__
  from benchmark.runner module
* pass to benchmark.runner._scenario_run_once dicts with endpoints
* refactors creation of openstack clients from endpoint dict
* refactors benchmark.utils._prepare_for_instance_ssh to work with
  endpoint dicts
* improve unit tests
* skip test_run_scenario_continuously_for_duration cause it produce a lot
  of race conditions in gates

TODO: Finish refactoring of ut

After this patch you will be able to use Rally as a benchmarking
tool=)

Change-Id: Ifa1e0e55516ac1ca5117203811c375b2c6aff0d7
Closes-Bug: #1282145

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2014-02-13 21:30:47.000000000', 'files': ['openstack_dashboard/api/neutron.py'], 'message': "1279979 Neutron TypeError when token invalid

When a neutron api-call is made, if the user's token is invalid, the
neutron client will return a type-error because no auth_url has been
provided.

TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for +: 'NoneType' and 'str'

This TypeError should really be an
neutronclient.common.exceptions.Unauthorized instead, which will get
percolated up via a password-base authentication failure.

Change-Id: I284e5cdf943fc63faf8509fdbe3caa45179d5f71
Closes-Bug: 1279979
"}]
commit_message:
1279979 Neutron TypeError when token invalid

When a neutron api-call is made, if the user's token is invalid, the
neutron client will return a type-error because no auth_url has been
provided.

TypeError: unsupported operand type(s) for +: 'NoneType' and 'str'

This TypeError should really be an
neutronclient.common.exceptions.Unauthorized instead, which will get
percolated up via a password-base authentication failure.

Change-Id: I284e5cdf943fc63faf8509fdbe3caa45179d5f71
Closes-Bug: 1279979

commit_message:
Fix duplicating of SQL queries in logs

Remove setting and passing echo parameter to create_engine()
function and replace it with configuring log level directly on
logger sqlalchemy.engine (this prevents adding of multiple
handlers writing to stderr to the root logger).

Change-Id: I799341a347cfcacdd27c70b91ed9b9e3cc70727f
Closes-Bug: #1278860
